comment11.text=\n\ Create\ the\ next\ pedestrian\ instance\ without\ coupling\ world\ logic\ to\ a\n\ specific\ Pedestrian\ subclass.\n
comment12.params=centerX\ centerY\ image
comment12.target=boolean\ isPedestrianAreaBlocked(int,\ int,\ greenfoot.GreenfootImage)
comment12.text=\n\ Codex\ change\:\ check\ whether\ a\ pedestrian\ image\ would\ overlap\ any\ blocked\n\ pixels\ in\ the\ background\ collision\ mask.\n\n\ @param\ centerX\ the\ actor\ center\ x-coordinate\ to\ test\n\ @param\ centerY\ the\ actor\ center\ y-coordinate\ to\ test\n\ @param\ image\ \ \ the\ actor\ image\ used\ to\ derive\ the\ bounding\ box\n\ @return\ true\ if\ any\ blocked\ mask\ pixel\ is\ covered\ by\ the\ actor\ bounds\n
comment13.params=lane
comment13.target=int\ getLaneY(int)
comment13.text=\n\ Given\ a\ lane\ number\ (zero-indexed),\ return\ the\ y\ position\n\ in\ the\ centre\ of\ the\ lane.\ (doesn't\ factor\ offset,\ so\n\ watch\ your\ offset,\ i.e.\ with\ Bus).\n\n\ @param\ lane\ the\ lane\ number\ (zero-indexed)\n\ @return\ int\ the\ y\ position\ of\ the\ lane's\ center,\ or\ -1\ if\ invalid\n
comment14.params=y
comment14.target=int\ getLane(int)
comment14.text=\n\ Given\ a\ y-position,\ return\ the\ lane\ number\ (zero-indexed).\n\ Note\ that\ the\ y-position\ must\ be\ valid,\ and\ you\ should\n\ include\ the\ offset\ in\ your\ calculations\ before\ calling\ this\ method.\n\ For\ example,\ if\ a\ Bus\ is\ in\ a\ lane\ at\ y\=100,\ but\ is\ offset\ by\ -20,\n\ it\ is\ actually\ in\ the\ lane\ located\ at\ y\=80,\ so\ you\ should\ send\n\ 80\ to\ this\ method,\ not\ 100.\n\n\ @param\ y\ -\ the\ y\ position\ of\ the\ lane\ the\ Vehicle\ is\ in\n\ @return\ int\ the\ lane\ number,\ zero-indexed\n\n
